>Description:
It would be convenient if one could select a font size
for the help desk separately from the font size used in 
the editors for editing code.  Currently they're controlled
by the same item in DrScheme/Preferences.  It's nice to
have global control.  perhaps specific sizes for the various
facets of DrScheme could be done relative to the global pref.
>How-To-Repeat:
Choose the DrScheme Preferences... dialog, select the "Font"
tab and change the font size to something really small.  Confirm
that this affects all fons in the system including the help desk
and this bug report dialog.
>Fix:
>Audit-Trail:
